Package io.github.retrooper.packetevents.event.impl

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    PacketHandshakeReceiveEvent
    The PacketHandshakeReceiveEvent event is fired whenever the a HANDSHAKE packet is received from a client.
    PacketLoginReceiveEvent
    The PacketLoginReceiveEvent event is fired whenever the a LOGIN packet is received from a client.
    PacketLoginSendEvent
    The PacketLoginSendEvent event is fired whenever the a LOGIN packet is being planned to be sent to the client.
    PacketPlayReceiveEvent
    The PacketPlayReceiveEvent event is fired whenever the a PLAY packet is received from any connected client.
    PacketPlaySendEvent
    The PacketPlaySendEvent event is fired whenever the a PLAY packet is about to be sent to a client.
    PacketStatusReceiveEvent
    The PacketStatusReceiveEvent event is fired whenever the server receives a STATUS packet from a client.
    PacketStatusSendEvent
    The PacketStatusSendEvent event is fired whenever the server wants to send a STATUS packet to a client.
    PlayerEjectEvent
    The PlayerEjectEvent event is fired whenever a player is ejected.
    PlayerInjectEvent
    The PlayerInjectEvent event is fired whenever a player is injected.
    PostPacketPlayReceiveEvent
    The PostPacketPlayReceiveEvent event is fired after all PacketEvents listeners finished processing the PacketPlayReceiveEvent.
    PostPacketPlaySendEvent
    The PostPacketPlaySendEvent event is fired after all PacketEvents listeners finished processing the PacketPlaySendEvent.
    PostPlayerInjectEvent
    The PostPlayerInjectEvent event is fired after a successful injection.
